Per-rule content ("What it does", "Why is this bad?", examples, configuration
references) in `*/rules/<slug>/index.md`, and text derived from it in the
compiled `guidelines.txt`, `style.md`, and `frameworks/*.md` files, is sourced
from the following upstream projects and carries their respective licenses:

- Rust guidelines — Microsoft Pragmatic Rust Guidelines, MIT
  https://microsoft.github.io/rust-guidelines/
- Python rules — Ruff, MIT
  https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/
- TypeScript & JavaScript rules — Oxlint / Oxc project, MIT
  https://oxc.rs/
